For instance, if I have this method:

```csharp
/// <summary>
/// Crashes the program.
/// </summary>
/// <exception cref="InvalidOperationException">when the C# compiler doesn't like you. Which is always.</exception>
public object Crash()
{
	throw new InvalidOperationException("The compiler doesn't like you.");
}
```

Then the generated tooltip from the XML comments correctly indicates that `InvalidOperationException` can be thrown, but it is missing the contents of the `<exception>` tag which state when the exception will be thrown. This would be useful information to have when consuming an API, so I can tell what would trigger an exception, which would inform me as to whether I need to catch it and what to do when I do catch it.

